<!-- Session 2: Energizing Breath (Wim Hof Style) -->
<!-- Duration Target: 20 minutes -->
<!-- 3 full rounds of 30 breaths + retention -->

<!-- Safety Warning -->
<p>
<s>Before we begin, an important safety notice.</s>
<break time="1000ms"/>
<s>This practice involves rapid deep breathing followed by breath retention.</s>
<break time="800ms"/>
<s>It can cause lightheadedness, tingling sensations, and temporary changes in consciousness.</s>
<break time="1200ms"/>
<s>These effects are normal and safe when practiced correctly.</s>
</p>

<break time="1500ms"/>

<p>
<s>However, you must never practice this technique near water.</s>
<break time="800ms"/>
<s>Never while driving or operating machinery.</s>
<break time="800ms"/>
<s>Never while standing until you know how your body responds.</s>
<break time="1200ms"/>
<s>If you have epilepsy, heart conditions, or are pregnant, do not practice this technique.</s>
</p>

<break time="1500ms"/>

<p>
<s>For this session, please lie down or sit comfortably with back support.</s>
<break time="1000ms"/>
<s>Make sure you're in a safe environment where you could briefly lose awareness without risk.</s>
<break time="1500ms"/>
<s>If you understand and accept these guidelines, let's continue.</s>
</p>

<break time="3000ms"/>

<!-- Opening -->
<p>
<s>Welcome to the Energizing Breath session.</s>
<break time="1500ms"/>
<s>This technique is based on ancient Tibetan practices, modernized by Wim Hof and validated by scientific research at Radboud University.</s>
<break time="1500ms"/>
<s>It has been shown to influence the autonomic nervous system and immune response in ways previously thought impossible.</s>
</p>

<break time="2000ms"/>

<p>
<s>What you're about to experience is powerful.</s>
<break time="1000ms"/>
<s>You'll feel energy surge through your body.</s>
<break time="800ms"/>
<s>You may feel tingling in your hands and face.</s>
<break time="800ms"/>
<s>Colors may appear more vivid.</s>
<break time="800ms"/>
<s>Your mind may become remarkably clear.</s>
<break time="1500ms"/>
<s>All of this is your own body's natural capacity, unlocked through breath.</s>
</p>

<break time="2500ms"/>

<!-- Preparation -->
<p>
<s>Let's prepare.</s>
<break time="1500ms"/>
<s>Settle into your position.</s>
<break time="1500ms"/>
<s>If you're wearing anything restrictive around your waist or chest, loosen it now.</s>
<break time="2000ms"/>
<s>Take a moment to blow your nose if needed. Clear airways are important.</s>
<break time="2500ms"/>
<s>Good.</s>
</p>

<break time="2000ms"/>

<p>
<s>The pattern we'll follow has three parts.</s>
<break time="1000ms"/>
<s>First, thirty deep, rapid breaths.</s>
<break time="800ms"/>
<s>Second, an exhale followed by a breath hold with empty lungs.</s>
<break time="800ms"/>
<s>Third, a deep inhale with a brief hold at the top.</s>
<break time="1500ms"/>
<s>That's one round. We'll complete three rounds together.</s>
</p>

<break time="2000ms"/>

<p>
<s>For the rapid breaths, breathe in fully through the nose or mouth, deep into the belly.</s>
<break time="1000ms"/>
<s>Then let the exhale fall naturally, without forcing it out.</s>
<break time="1000ms"/>
<s>No pause between breaths. Continuous flow.</s>
<break time="1000ms"/>
<s>The pace will be about one breath every two seconds.</s>
</p>

<break time="2500ms"/>

<!-- Round 1 -->
<p>
<s>Round one.</s>
<break time="2000ms"/>
<s>When you're ready, begin with me.</s>
<break time="1500ms"/>
<s>Deep breath in.</s>
<break time="1200ms"/>
<s>And let it go.</s>
</p>

<break time="1000ms"/>

